abstract: Commissioners in counties around the nation, including North Dakota, are weighing whether to admit more refugees.
snippet: Commissioners in counties around the nation, including North Dakota, are weighing whether to admit more refugees.
lead_paragraph: Commissioners in one North Dakota county voted on Monday night to continue accepting refugees, a split decision that came about because of a Trump administration policy that gives local officials the extraordinary option to reject people fleeing persecution.

abstract: Congressional Democrats and the White House are on the cusp of an agreement on revisions to the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement.
snippet: Congressional Democrats and the White House are on the cusp of an agreement on revisions to the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic lawmakers are nearing an agreement to bring the revised North American free trade deal to a vote after securing additional labor, enforcement and other provisions and winning the support of top labor leaders.

abstract: Olga Neuwirth’s adaptation of Virginia Woolf is the first work by a woman to be performed by the Vienna State Opera.
snippet: Olga Neuwirth’s adaptation of Virginia Woolf is the first work by a woman to be performed by the Vienna State Opera.
lead_paragraph: VIENNA — Olga Neuwirth’s “Orlando” had made history even before its world premiere at the Vienna State Opera here on Sunday: It would be the first work by a female composer to be performed by this storied company.

abstract: In a legal complaint, Amazon said the president had attacked it behind the scenes to harm its C.E.O., Jeff Bezos, “his perceived political enemy.”
snippet: In a legal complaint, Amazon said the president had attacked it behind the scenes to harm its C.E.O., Jeff Bezos, “his perceived political enemy.”
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Amazon said in a legal complaint unsealed on Monday that it had lost a $10 billion cloud computing contract with the Pentagon because President Trump used “improper pressure” to divert the contract from the company to harm its chief executive, Jeff Bezos.

headline_main: Amazon Accuses Trump of ‘Improper Pressure’ on JEDI Contract

abstract: Uncouth he may be, but he’s not unfamiliar.
snippet: Uncouth he may be, but he’s not unfamiliar.
lead_paragraph: Like more than a few Americans, I used to read President Donald Trump’s tweets with trepidation. No modern president had ever expressed himself publicly in this manner, and the universal reaction seemed to be a mixture of horror and consternation.

abstract: A long-awaited report by the Justice Department’s inspector general delivers a scathing critique of the F.B.I.’s handling of a wiretap application but also punctures many conspiracy theories.
snippet: A long-awaited report by the Justice Department’s inspector general delivers a scathing critique of the F.B.I.’s handling of a wiretap application but also punctures many conspiracy theories.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — F.B.I. officials had sufficient reason to open the investigation into links between Russia and Trump campaign aides in 2016 and acted without political bias, a long-awaited report said on Monday, but it concluded that the inquiry was a rushed and dysfunctional process marked by serious errors in documents related to a wiretap.

abstract: The documents, obtained by The Washington Post, paint a stark picture of missteps and failures in the American effort to pacify and rebuild the country.
snippet: The documents, obtained by The Washington Post, paint a stark picture of missteps and failures in the American effort to pacify and rebuild the country.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Prominent American officials concealed pessimistic assessments about the long-running military campaign in Afghanistan, according to thousands of pages of documents published by The Washington Post on Monday. Taken together, the documents paint a stark picture of missteps and failures.

abstract: The House Judiciary Committee held a hearing Monday considering the case for and against impeaching President Trump. Our reporters provided live coverage and analysis during presentations by Democratic and Republican lawyers on evidence from the inquiry.

abstract: The U.S. is trying to preserve a diplomatic opening with Kim Jong-un, even as North Korea dismisses President Trump as a “heedless and erratic old man.”
snippet: The U.S. is trying to preserve a diplomatic opening with Kim Jong-un, even as North Korea dismisses President Trump as a “heedless and erratic old man.”
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration has refused to support a move by members of the United Nations Security Council to hold a discussion Tuesday on North Korea’s rampant human rights abuses, effectively blocking the meeting for the second year in a row.
